9700.name: Water Dragon Claw
9700.description: An item given by a Fafurion Family. It may be used to save Parme. Water Dragon Claw

9701.description: This key can seal a Magic Field. Box Key

9702.name: Caravaner's Remedy
9702.description: This can cool down the heat of the Hellbound Desert. Caravan's Secret Medicine

9710.description: This key can open the Katenar Gate. Leopold Key

9711.name: Gate Key: Prediction
9711.description: This key can open the Gate of Prediction. Gate Key of Prediction

9712.name: Gate Key: Massive Cavern
9712.description: This key can open the Massive Cavern Gate. Gate Key of Nornil

9713.name: Nornil's Power
9713.description: Use it at locations marked in yellow on the map. Nornil's Power

9714.name: Key of the Evil Eye
9714.description: The keymaster in town has the key you need to enter the Steel Citadel. Gate Key of Darkness

9715.name: Giant Key
9715.description: This key is the size of a human arm. What can it be used for? Gate Key of Destruction

9716.name: Scroll of Escape: Kamael Village
9716.description: This scroll magically relocates you to Kamael Village. Scroll of Escape to Talking Island

9717.name: Information on Eranus
9717.description: Double-click this document for more information on Eranus.

9718.name: Report on the Crimson Duchess
9718.description: This report about Beleth's minion, the Crimson Duchess, whom you may encounter while making a pilgrimage to the Tablet. Double-click it for more information.

9719.name: List of Attackers
9719.description: This is a list of the angels who recently attacked. Double-click it for more information.

9720.name: Warrior's Sword
9720.description: This sword identifies its wielder as a Warrior of Kamael.

9721.name: Freezer
9721.description: This machine can be acquired from Information Broker Mist. Take it to Master Duroga.

9740.name: Halisha's Mark
9740.description: This cursed mark summons the minion of Halisha.

9741.name: Halisha's Mark
9741.description: This cursed mark summons the minion of Halisha.

9742.name: Halisha's Mark
9742.description: This cursed mark summons the minion of Halisha.

9743.name: Shining Medallion
9743.description: This medal is possessed by high level angels.

9746.name: Commander's Feather
9746.description: A feather pulled out of a commander-level Muertos.

9747.name: Crimson Spider Claw
9747.description: Take this claw to Second Hierarch Perwan.

9748.name: Muertos Feather
9748.description: This feather can be obtained by hunting the Muertos. Take it to merchant Treabi.

9749.name: Felim Lizardman Head
9749.description: A Head obtained after killing the Felim Lizardman.

9750.name: Venomous Spider's Leg
9750.description: This leg is obtained by killing a giant spider.

9751.name: Tumran Bugbear Heart
9751.description: The heart of a Tumran Bugbear.

9752.name: Shubain's Recommendation
9752.description: A letter of recommendation written by Master Shubain of Gludin. Take it to Gwain in the Town of Gludio.

9753.name: Gwain's Recommendation
9753.description: A letter of recommendation written by Master Gwain of Gludio. Give it to a grand master of the Kamael Guild to change your job.

9754.name: Breka Orc Head
9754.description: A Head obtained after killing a Breka Orc.

9755.name: Message Plate
9755.description: A message plate collected from a Road Scavenger.

9756.name: Report - East
9756.description: A report discovered on the corpse of a Dead Seeker on the Execution Grounds.

9757.name: Report - North
9757.description: A report discovered on the corpse of a Stakato Drone in the Cruma Marshlands.

9758.name: Harkilgamed's Letter
9758.description: Harkilgamed asks that this letter be delivered to Master Tenain.

9759.name: Tenain's Recommendation
9759.description: Take this letter of recommendation written by Master Tenain to Master Orkurus in the Town of Oren.

9760.name: Orkurus' Recommendation
9760.description: A letter of recommendation written by Master Orkurus in the Town of Oren. Give it to a grand master of the Kamael Guild to change your job.

9761.name: Frozen Cell Samples
9761.description: Magister Justin requires these cells for his life energy studies.

9762.name: Orders
9762.description: These Ol Mahum Orders can be found in the deserted campground. Collect them, as well as Ol Mahum Organization Charts, and give them to Kamael Master Sione.

9763.name: Organization Chart
9763.description: This Ol Mahum Organization Chart can be found in the deserted campground. Collect them, as well as the Ol Mahum Orders, and give them to Kamael Master Sione.

9764.name: Gobie's Orders
9764.description: Based on documents of the Ol Mahum, these orders outline the strategy for facing them. It should be delivered to Kamael Master Gobie.

9765.name: Letter to the Humans
9765.description: This letter, written to the Human allies of the Kamael, should be delivered to Captain Bathis in the town of Gludio.

9766.name: Humans' Reply
9766.description: This letter from Captain Bathis should be delivered to Master Gobie.

9767.name: Letter to the Dark Elves
9767.description: This letter, written to the Dark Elven allies of the Kamael, should be delivered to Grand Master Tobias in the Town of Gludio.

9768.name: Dark Elves' Reply
9768.description: This letter from the Dark Elf Grand Master Tobias should be delivered to Kamael Master Gobie.

9769.name: Report to Sione
9769.description: This report, written by Gobie on the progress of negotiations between the Humans and Dark Elves, should be delivered to Master Sione.

9770.name: Empty Soul Crystal
9770.description: Ol Mahum Officer Tak can be imprisoned in this crystal.

9771.name: Tak's Captured Soul
9771.description: Ol Mahum Officer Tak is imprisoned within this crystal. Take it to Master Gobie for interrogation.

9772.name: Steelrazor Evaluation
9772.description: An evaluation of the Kamael special forces, Steelrazor. Give it to a nearby Kamael Grand Master to complete the class transfer to a Warder.

9773.name: Enmity Crystal
9773.description: Magister Clayton has been searching for this material. If you bring him a sufficient amount, he will give you information.

9774.name: Enmity Crystal Core
9774.description: This magic item is made from Enmity Crystals. Give it to Blacksmith Poitan of Dion.

9775.name: Manuscript Page
9775.description: Warehouse Keeper Holvas is searching for these pages. Collect them all and give them to him.

9776.name: Encoded Page on the Ancient Race
9776.description: This coded document discusses new races. Holvas says that Kamael Grand Master Meldina can decode it.

9777.name: Kamael Inquisitor Trainee Mark
9777.description: Show this to Selsia, the head of the Kamael Intelligence Agency, to take the class transfer test.

9778.name: Fragment of Attack Orders
9778.description: Fragments of attack orders gathered by killing Grandis. Collect all the fragments to discover who is behind the attack.

9779.name: Grandis' Attack Orders
9779.description: Complete attack orders which say the attack was requested by Ivory Tower Magister Gaius. Let's interrogate Gaius with the request.

9780.name: Manashen's Talisman
9780.description: Pieces of a control charm obtained by killing Manashen. You may find out who controlled Manashen if you can find every piece of the charm.

9781.name: Research on the Giants and the Ancient Race
9781.description: This research document on the Giants' relationship to the hidden race was carried by Beleth's minion, the Crimson Duchess. Take it to Master Selsia.

9782.name: Kamael Inquisitor Mark
9782.description: This mark proves that you have successfully passed the Inquisitor test. Show it to a Kamael Grand Master to be transferred to Arbalester.

9783.name: Echo Crystal of Free Thought
9783.description: This crystal originally belonged to the Mother of Witches. Can be used to help a witch recover her memories.

9784.name: Parme's Letter
9784.description: This letter from the Witch of Water Dragon following the recovery of her memory should be delivered to Priest Karnis.

9785.name: Refined Crystal Sample
9785.description: This magic material sought by a Wizard who was sent to the Ivory Tower to keep Hellbound Island under observation. Give it to him and try to talk with him.

9786.name: Stabilized Ectoplasm
9786.description: Hardin requires this material for his studies on transformation magic. Deliver it to him to enable him to carry on with his experiments.

9787.name: Ectoplasm
9787.description: This material is necessary for creating stabilized ectoplasm, which can be used in transformation magic.

9788.name: Hardin's Instructions
9788.description: Written by Hardin concerning transformation magic, this should be delivered to Magister Clayton of Dion.

9789.name: Glass Jaguar Crystal
9789.description: One of the materials requested by Hardin. Deliver it to Magister Clayton.

9790.name: Blank Sealbook
9790.description: This empty, sealed letter can store powers and seals for Hardin's transformation magic. It should be delivered to Hardin.

9791.name: Transformation Sealbook: Onyx Beast
9791.description: A sealed letter that carries powers and seals of initial transformation magic. If you give it to 2nd floor of the Ivory Tower to the Wizard of Transformation, you can be transformed.

9792.name: Warehouse Manifest
9792.description: A supply confirmation for a warehouse in Kamael. It should be delivered to Zerstorer Marcela.

9793.name: Grocery Store Manifest
9793.description: A supply confirmation for a Grocery Store in Kamael. It should be delivered to Zerstorer Marcela.

9794.name: Weapon Shop Manifest
9794.description: A supply confirmation for a Weapon Shop in Kamael. It should be delivered to Zerstorer Marcela.

9795.name: Supply Report
9795.description: Zerstorer Marcela's report on supplies. It should be delivered to Hierarch Casca.

9796.name: Hills of Gold Monster Claw
9796.description: The claw of a monster found in the Hills of Gold. It should be taken to Zerstorer Marcela.

9797.name: Dungeon Leader Mark
9797.description: A mark that signifies the leader of the monsters which appear in the Dungeon. It should be delivered to a Manager at the Fortress Monster Prison Camp.

9798.name: Fragment of the Dungeon Leader Mark
9798.description: A badge fragment that signifies a leader of the monsters which appear in the Dungeon. It should be delivered to a Manager at the Fortress Monster Prison Camp.

9799.name: Wolf Tail
9799.description: This tail possesses rich, luxurious fur.
